dA
s_p = 0.9cm
s_m = 0.95cm
ds = s_m- s_p = 0.05cm
dA = s_m * ds = .95cm * .05cm = 0.475cm^2
x
A(x)=x^2
A
A'(x)={dA\over dx}=2x.
\Delta x
x=x_0
\Delta A
 {dA\over dx}\biggl|_{x=x_0}\approx {\Delta A\over \Delta x}. 
x
x=x_0=.9
x=.95
\Delta x=.05
\Delta A\approx {dA\over dx}\biggl|_{x=.9} \cdot\,\Delta x=2(.9)\cdot(.05)=.09\,{\text {cm}}^2
A = \ell^2
\ell
\mathrm{d}A = 2\ell\,\mathrm{d}\ell
\mathrm{d}A
\mathrm{d}\ell
\ell = 0.9
\mathrm{d}\ell = 0.05
\frac{\mathrm{d}A}{\mathrm{d}\ell} = 2\ell
\mathrm{d}A = 2\times 0.9 \times 0.05 = 0.09
